cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper deals with the algorithmic problem of finding vertex disjoint paths in planar digraphs. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely category as the paper specifically focuses on the class of upward planar digraphs, which is a well-studied class of planar graphs in computational geometry. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper involves proving NP-completeness and fixed-parameter tractability of a graph problem, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph theory and finding paths in graphs, which are topics relevant to game theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper involves proving the complexity of a graph problem and analyzing the parameter dependence of an algorithm, which are topics in computational complexity theory.
